node.text:
@thelistshowtv  interviewed me and asked me for some tips to give parents whose children’s are returning back to school after remote learning.

Things are constantly changing and I don’t have all of the answers but hopefully some of these tips are helpful to you :)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by MoNique Waters ♡🦋 on July 22, 2021 tagging @getyourteachon. May be an image of 1 person, standing, balloon and text that says 'G Y T KINDERGARTEN KIND ferst FIRST grade GET GET TEACH TEACH ON #GET YOURTEACHON O #GETYOURTEACHON'.

node.text:
✨✨
You wanna know what I love about this week, about this conference and all of the amazing educators here?!?

I love that we are able to collaborate, learn, grow, step out of our comfort zone all while having the time of our lives.

I leave here with new strategies, content, lessons, materials and resources that are all research based and effective all while making new friends and having sooo much fun!

I love that I feel valuable and appreciated!
I love that I am engaged and interested in what I am actually learning.
I love the energy!
I love all the love.

@getyourteachon is more than just a PD it is how I fill my cup, how I refuel, and how I grow as an educator and a person.

Having the opportunity to present this year made the experience next level amazing. I love teaching and learning and I’m just so thankful and blessed to be here.
.
.
#teachersofinstagram #teachersfollowteachers #getyourteachon #gytoxorlando

node.text:
🏋🏽‍♀️💪🏽
My heart is beyond full!
Having the opportunity to speak in a room filled with so many amazing, passionate, beautiful educators was unbelievable. Y’all truly are UNSTOPPABLE! 

I am beyond honored!

So excited for all the MAGIC still to come.
.
.
.
📸 @david_erickson_photography 
#getyourteachon #gytoxorlando

node.text:
💕☀️

Hello Beautiful People. The way I start my day has played a huge role in my personal journey for self-care. 

That’s why I really enjoy the app UpWeGo that offers virtual classes, live workshops, and uplifting daily content.

 Their focus on fitness, mindfulness, creativity, self-care & more leaves something for everyone. 

 UpWeGo lets you know that you are not alone. You are able to reflect and share with support from a thoughtful community.

Right now upwego is offering frontline workers (teachers yes that you) one year free. They are also offering one month free with promo code: MYJOURNEY

Remember your journey is up to you.

#UPWEGO #SPONSORED

Xo MoMo 💕

💕🏫
Can we just smile at my very first classroom at my previous district. I loved this space.

Fun Fact I had the biggest room in the school and I really used every bit of it.

This classroom was filled with so much love and a lot of stuff.

Although it was large there was no built in storage which required me to be very organized!

Putting things that you don’t use daily but know you will need at some point in large labeled bins really helps. When you need that item you just grab the bin and there it is!

To learn more teacher tips, register for the Classroom Environment + Design Conference using the link in my bio!

You’ll have immediate, lifetime access to the sessions. Tickets are only for sale until July 21, so be sure to grab them now!

#classroomtip #classroomdecor #classroomdesign #classroomsetup #classroommakeover #classroomorganization #teachersofinstagram #teachersofig

node.text:
✍🏽🖍
Full Video on IGTV.

Here is another video of a chant we do. If you seen my “detailed sentence” chant it’s to the same tune on purpose. We learn this one first then the sentence one later on.
.
.
.

In kindergarten I really try to stress the importance of having a detailed picture.

Early this year I saw a blog post with an anchor chart similar to the one I have on my board.

I really liked the idea of teaching my students to include all 5 senses in their illustrations.
This has really helped them with adding detail to their work.

I of course made up a simple little chant for us to do when we review.

I would love to know some of the ways you teach your students to include detail in their illustrations and writing!!!
.
.
